area_name: Across From Cenotaph aka Sea of Tranquility

content.description:
This is another route on this unknown crag.  It ascends a groove, not the black one.  The crux seemed to be at the top.  This info comes from terse notes from 10 years ago.

Anyone know the name of the route? history? This is posted here, since I'm curious & found these notes scribbled and no good answers.

Please don't bolt this.
content.protection: It is best to TR this.

content.description:
This is a brief description from terse notes from a decade ago.  On the right side, clip a 1/4" bolt, a 3/8" bolt, then use #1, #0 Friends, #4BD wire, #3 Friend, pass a tree, go to a higher tree.  Rap.

Anyone know the name of the route? history?  This is posted here, since I'm curious & found these notes scribbled and no good answers.
content.location: This is on the right side of the crag.

content.description:
This is another route on this unknown crag. It ascends an obvious, low-angled, black groove.  It was quite enjoyable.  This info comes from terse notes from 10 years ago.

Anyone know the name of the route? history? This is posted here, since I'm curious & found these notes scribbled and no good answers.

Please don't bolt this.
content.location: There is an obvious black groove, probably a water streak in the center-left side of this little crag.
